    "body": "https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/master/src/modules/username.rs#L46\n\nThis needs to be a `&&`, not a `||`, at least for the purposes of fixing my config.\n\nHowever, `Context::detect_env_vars` is actually fundamentally insufficient for expression the logic described in the username module. This is because the function's return value *cannot* differentiate between \"A negated variable is set\" and \"No non-negated variables are set\".\n\nThis means `detect_env_vars` actually overrules all other detection mechanisms, instead of adding to them and only overruling if a negated variable was found.\n\nI can try to make a PR for this but given that this affects in principle almost every single module I may just add an extra method to `Context`.",
